Detection Logic

Detect suspicious shell spawned by SSH session.

Splunk Query
index=linux sourcetype=process
(parent_process=sshd OR parent_process=ssh)
| search process IN ("bash","sh","nc","python","perl")
| stats count by host user process parent_process

What This Does

Looks for processes spawned from sshd

Filters for commonly abused binaries

Shows which user executed them

Why

Attackers often execute:

bash
sh
python reverse shells
nc backdoors

Typical attacker behavior:

SSH Login
     ↓
Spawn shell
     ↓
Reconnaissance
     ↓
Download tools
     ↓
Persistence / lateral movement

Common suspicious processes launched after SSH:

bash
sh
python
perl
nc
curl
wget
socat
